SECTION 1. This act is known and may be cited as the "Hurricane Helene Rapid
Response Act."
SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 9, Chapter 4, Part 2, is amended by
adding the following as a new section:
9-4-215. Appropriation fund for Hurricane Helene relief for impacted local
governments.
(a) There is created within the state treasury a Hurricane Helene county relief
fund, hereinafter the "fund," to be administered by the department of finance and
administration for the benefit of counties recovering from Hurricane Helene. The
department shall award grants from the fund to county governing bodies in accordance
with this section.
(b) It is the intent of the general assembly that the fund is funded by an
appropriation of fifty million dollars ($50,000,000) for fiscal year 2025-2026, and may be
funded by additional appropriations in subsequent fiscal years.
(c) A county that receives a grant from the fund must use the grant money for
any purpose related to infrastructure, remediation, repair or replacement of improved or
unimproved public or private real or personal property, and other general purposes
related to county recovery efforts in the aftermath of Hurricane Helene.
(d) Subject to appropriations, on July 2, 2025, the department shall award grants
from the fund as follows:
